RasterFunctionTemplate.Name: NDVI Colormap
RasterFunctionTemplate.Description: Normalized difference vegetation index (NDVI) with colormap. Dark green represents vigorous vegetation and brown represents sparse vegetation. It is computed as (b5 - b4) / (b5 + b4) and is suitable for vegetation, land cover and plant health monitoring.

Function.Name: Colormap Function
Function.Description: Transforms the pixel values to display the raster data as either a grayscale or a red, green, blue (RGB) image, based on a color map or a color ramp.

Function.Name: NDVI Function
Function.Description: Calculates the Normalized Vegetation Differential Index (NDVI) values using a two-band raster consisting of the Red and near infrared bands.
